19
20 WHEREAS, former Speaker of the House of Representatives Benny Charles
21 Petrus, formerly of Stuttgart, Arkansas, passed away Friday, May 17, 2024, at
22 the age of sixty-seven (67); and
23
24 WHEREAS, former Speaker Petrus was born November 23, 1956, in
25 Stuttgart, to Bernard and Earline Petrus; and
26
27 WHEREAS, former Speaker Petrus lived in Stuttgart his entire life and
28 was a 1975 graduate of Stuttgart High School; and
29
30 WHEREAS, former Speaker Petrus attended the University of Central
31 Arkansas in Conway and became a successful businessman, owning several car
32 dealerships in Stuttgart, Arkansas, owning several farms and other
33 businesses, and serving as President and Chief Executive Officer of Adams
34 Fertilizer Equipment Company in DeWitt, Arkansas; and
35
36 WHEREAS, former Speaker Petrus's life was a family affair, reflected in
